Objective:
Verify that a user can complete the full project management workflow in the application without errors.

Preconditions:

Application deployed in test environment

User account exists and has proper permissions

Sample project data is available

Test Steps:

Login – Sign in with valid credentials

Enter SRS – Upload or input the Software Requirements Specification

Verify Product Backlog – Check that backlog items appear correctly

Create Sprints – Set up a sprint with start and end dates

Add Stories to Sprint – Assign backlog items to the sprint

Verify Charts – Check burndown, velocity, and other project charts

Update/Track Progress – Mark tasks complete and verify updates in charts

Logout – Sign out from the application

Expected Results:

User logs in successfully

SRS is saved and displayed correctly

Product backlog reflects all items accurately

Sprint is created with correct dates and items

Charts show accurate, real-time data

Progress updates reflect in both sprint and charts

No UI errors or broken elements

Logout completes without issues
